description.narrative:
Vision: By March 2016, the villagers in Dak Glong district, Dak Nong province will be empowered to raise their voice and to be heard. They become active and innovative in community development activities, contribute to the improvement and the effectiveness of NewRural National Target Program, and result in reducing the household poverty rates, enhancing political stability, and creating wider impacts within and beyond the province.
The project aims to achieve the following concrete objectives:
- To create spaces for villagers to apply their learning and to exercise collective actions;
- To build capacity and self-confidence of villagers in 'claimed spaces' in economic development through supporting and replicating farmer-initiated livelihoods models;
- To promote people's self-esteem and to create opportunities to exercise power in claimed spaces in cultural and social development by supporting cultural diversity and solidarity initiatives of local people;
- To enhance people's active roles in community development and participation in 'invited spaces' utilizing existing legal platforms for dialogues, and enhancing representative roles of Farmers Union;
- To raise public awareness and recognition on rights and capacities of ethnic minorities, and their empowerment processes by engaging media in promoting project methodology and results.
